        <h5>What is the Jesuit Science Network (JSN)?</h5>

        <p>
          The Jesuit Science Network is a biographical database on Jesuit scholars in the early modern sciences,
          encompassing the period between the foundation of the Society of Jesus in 1540 and the first few decades after
          the suppression of the order in 1773. After its scheduled launch in summer/fall 2016, it will be a publicly
          available online tool that will not only allow the display of biographical data of more than 1000 Jesuit
          scholars in early modern sciences, but also offer complex searches into who was doing what, when, and where.
        </p>

